587
00:35:10.772 --> 00:35:12.592
So going to the next talk.

588
00:35:13.652 --> 00:35:17.332
So now we welcome Dr. Zenara Shah from Roseville Park Comprehensive

589
00:35:17.412 --> 00:35:18.172
Cancer Center.

590
00:35:22.892 --> 00:35:26.492
Good afternoon, everyone. On behalf of my co-authors, I'm pleased to present the

591
00:35:26.552 --> 00:35:27.572
findings of our study.

592
00:35:28.692 --> 00:35:29.832
These are my disclosures.

593
00:35:31.192 --> 00:35:35.172
Metastatic colorectal cancer remain associated with poor long-term outcome

594
00:35:35.232 --> 00:35:37.292
despite advances in systemic therapy.

595
00:35:37.772 --> 00:35:41.332
Approximately 80% to 85% of colorectal cancer are

596
00:35:41.412 --> 00:35:45.252
microsatellite stable, a subgroup with limited effective treatment options.

597
00:35:45.792 --> 00:35:49.732
Within microsatellite stable disease, HER2 amplification occur in 2% to

598
00:35:49.852 --> 00:35:53.692
4% of cases and defines a biologically distinct subset

599
00:35:53.752 --> 00:35:57.742
characterized by primary resistance to anti-EGFR therapy and

600
00:35:57.832 --> 00:35:59.992
sensitivity to HER2-targeted agents.

601
00:36:00.852 --> 00:36:04.812
This identifies an aggressive chemotherapy-refractory population in which

602
00:36:04.832 --> 00:36:06.312
targeted therapy may improve

603
00:36:06.472 --> 00:36:10.004
outcomes.Trastuzumab

604
00:36:10.044 --> 00:36:13.804
deruxtecan has demonstrated substantial activity in HER2-positive

605
00:36:13.904 --> 00:36:17.814
metastatic colorectal cancer. In DESTINY-CRC01,

606
00:36:17.944 --> 00:36:21.764
among heavily pretreated patients who had received greater than two prior

607
00:36:21.784 --> 00:36:25.363
lines of therapy, trastuzumab deruxtecan achieved an overall

608
00:36:25.404 --> 00:36:28.964
response rate of 45% and median overall

609
00:36:29.024 --> 00:36:32.804
survival of 15.5 months. However, the role of

610
00:36:32.824 --> 00:36:36.124
trastuzumab deruxtecan earlier in the treatment course remains

611
00:36:36.184 --> 00:36:40.004
unclear. Whether these benefits extend to less heavily pretreated

612
00:36:40.084 --> 00:36:43.724
real-world patients, particularly in the second-line setting, remain an

613
00:36:43.824 --> 00:36:45.564
important unanswered question.

614
00:36:47.784 --> 00:36:51.344
To address this gap, our primary objective was to compare real-world

615
00:36:51.504 --> 00:36:54.884
overall survival between trastuzumab deruxtecan and standard

616
00:36:54.924 --> 00:36:57.844
chemotherapy in patients with microsatellite stable,

617
00:36:58.084 --> 00:37:00.724
HER2-amplified metastatic colorectal cancer.

618
00:37:01.364 --> 00:37:05.264
From a clinical perspective, we aim to answer a key question, whether

619
00:37:05.324 --> 00:37:09.184
trastuzumab deruxtecan improve long-term survival when used earlier

620
00:37:09.224 --> 00:37:12.204
in the treatment course, specifically in the second-line setting.

621
00:37:13.924 --> 00:37:17.744
We conducted a retrospective cohort study using the TriNetX US

622
00:37:17.824 --> 00:37:21.444
network from 2010 through 2025. Cohorts were

623
00:37:21.464 --> 00:37:24.934
defined by the lines of therapy at which patient initiated either

624
00:37:24.964 --> 00:37:27.744
trastuzumab deruxtecan or standard chemotherapy.

625
00:37:28.444 --> 00:37:32.264
Eligible patients were adults with HER2-amplified microsatellite stable

626
00:37:32.324 --> 00:37:36.264
metastatic colorectal cancer. Patient received either second-line

627
00:37:36.344 --> 00:37:40.284
chemotherapy including FOLFOX, FOLFIRI, or CAPOX, with

628
00:37:40.324 --> 00:37:43.304
or without bevacizumab or trastuzumab deruxtecan.

629
00:37:43.944 --> 00:37:47.824
Patients with prior exposure to anti-EGFR or anti-HER2 therapy

630
00:37:47.884 --> 00:37:48.604
were excluded.

631
00:37:50.664 --> 00:37:54.264
Before matching, baseline differences were observed between the two cohorts.

632
00:37:54.824 --> 00:37:58.804
Patients receiving standard chemotherapy had highly higher rates of

633
00:37:58.844 --> 00:38:02.484
comorbidities, including chronic obstructive pulmonary disease and a greater

634
00:38:02.584 --> 00:38:06.224
burden of lung metastasis. BRAF mutations were also

635
00:38:06.264 --> 00:38:08.784
modestly more frequent in the chemotherapy cohort.

636
00:38:09.204 --> 00:38:13.064
Importantly, all patients across both groups were HER2 IHC3

637
00:38:13.124 --> 00:38:13.644
positive.

638
00:38:15.224 --> 00:38:18.753
Prior treatment exposure was otherwise broadly comparable between cohorts.

639
00:38:19.304 --> 00:38:23.084
These imbalance underscored the need for adjustment, which we addressed using

640
00:38:23.104 --> 00:38:24.904
propensity score matching.

641
00:38:28.204 --> 00:38:31.884
Matching variables included age, sex, comorbidities, metastatic

642
00:38:31.924 --> 00:38:34.104
disease burden, and prior treatment exposure.

643
00:38:34.664 --> 00:38:38.544
After matching, excellent covariate balance was achieved, with all standardized

644
00:38:38.584 --> 00:38:42.544
mean difference less than 0.1. The final matched cohort

645
00:38:42.584 --> 00:38:45.913
included 1870 patients in each group for comparative

646
00:38:45.964 --> 00:38:47.004
analysis.

647
00:38:48.784 --> 00:38:52.584
Overall survival was analyzed using Kaplan-Meier with log-rank testing,

648
00:38:53.044 --> 00:38:56.044
and adjusted hazard ratio was estimated using Cox model.

649
00:38:56.524 --> 00:38:59.984
Statistical significance was set at a two-sided P-value less than

650
00:39:00.204 --> 00:39:03.484
0.05, with safety outcome assessed descriptively.

651
00:39:07.184 --> 00:39:10.644
In the matched cohort, early overall survival was similar between

652
00:39:10.944 --> 00:39:14.244
groups with one-year overall survival of 85% for

653
00:39:14.324 --> 00:39:17.764
chemotherapy and 83% for trastuzumab deruxtecan.

654
00:39:18.444 --> 00:39:22.324
Over time, the survival curves separated, demonstrating improved long-term

655
00:39:22.444 --> 00:39:24.444
outcomes with trastuzumab deruxtecan.

656
00:39:25.044 --> 00:39:28.784
At five years, overall survival was 58% with trastuzumab

657
00:39:28.804 --> 00:39:31.684
deruxtecan versus 49% with chemotherapy.

658
00:39:32.364 --> 00:39:36.284
Consistent with these findings, standard chemotherapy was associated with a

659
00:39:36.364 --> 00:39:39.964
higher risk of mortality compared with trastuzumab deruxtecan,

660
00:39:40.324 --> 00:39:44.304
hazard ratio 1.14. Given the early curve crossing, the

661
00:39:44.324 --> 00:39:46.344
hazard ratio should be interpreted with caution.

662
00:39:46.384 --> 00:39:49.904
However, the sustained late separation supports a long-term survival

663
00:39:49.964 --> 00:39:52.364
advantage with trastuzumab deruxtecan.

664
00:39:55.064 --> 00:39:59.054
We observed slightly higher rates of all grade interstitial lung disease and heart

665
00:39:59.124 --> 00:40:02.004
failure than those reported in clinical trials.

666
00:40:02.413 --> 00:40:06.184
Specifically, interstitial lung disease occurred in 12% of patients, while

667
00:40:06.264 --> 00:40:09.764
heart failure occurred in 9%. Importantly, these were

668
00:40:09.904 --> 00:40:13.764
EHR-coded events and were not independently drug adjudicated.

669
00:40:14.364 --> 00:40:18.304
These findings support careful cardiopulmonary monitoring, including symptom

670
00:40:18.384 --> 00:40:21.824
surveillance, interval chest imaging, and echocardiography when

671
00:40:22.044 --> 00:40:23.284
clinically appropriate.

672
00:40:25.543 --> 00:40:29.264
Comparative toxicity profile remained distinct between treatment groups.

673
00:40:29.644 --> 00:40:33.004
Hematological adverse events were broadly similar between treatment groups

674
00:40:33.044 --> 00:40:36.344
including anemia, thrombocytopenia, and decreased neutrophil count.

675
00:40:36.824 --> 00:40:40.104
Fatigue and vomiting were more frequent with trastuzumab deruxtecan.

676
00:40:40.524 --> 00:40:43.104
Diarrhea occurred more often in chemotherapy cohort.

677
00:40:43.624 --> 00:40:46.984
Overall, these findings highlight the need for proactive monitoring of

678
00:40:47.004 --> 00:40:50.904
cytopenias and supportive care when using trastuzumab deruxtecan in

679
00:40:50.944 --> 00:40:51.844
routine practice.

680
00:40:53.644 --> 00:40:55.764
Our study has several important strengths.

681
00:40:56.024 --> 00:40:59.824
We used a large, multi-institutional real-world data set, achieved

682
00:40:59.904 --> 00:41:03.544
well-balanced cohort through propensity score matching, and had sufficient

683
00:41:03.664 --> 00:41:07.284
follow-up to evaluate long-term outcomes, including five-year overall

684
00:41:07.384 --> 00:41:11.184
survival. However, some of the limitations should be acknowledged.

685
00:41:11.584 --> 00:41:15.184
As an EHR and ICD-10 coding-based analysis, there is

686
00:41:15.224 --> 00:41:19.064
potential for misclassification, limited treatment granularity such

687
00:41:19.084 --> 00:41:23.064
as dose modification or treatment intensity, and adverse events that

688
00:41:23.084 --> 00:41:25.564
were not independently drug adjudicated.

689
00:41:26.004 --> 00:41:29.884
In addition, cancer-specific survival and progression-free survival could not

690
00:41:29.964 --> 00:41:30.644
be assessed.

691
00:41:32.384 --> 00:41:36.264
Clinically, these findings suggest that trastuzumab deruxtecan may be considered

692
00:41:36.324 --> 00:41:39.144
a second-line option for patients with microsatellite stable,

693
00:41:39.484 --> 00:41:42.084
HER2-amplified metastatic colorectal cancer.

694
00:41:42.764 --> 00:41:46.184
This result also support earlier integration of antibody drug

695
00:41:46.224 --> 00:41:50.144
conjugates in this population, consistent with observations in other

696
00:41:50.204 --> 00:41:54.054
solid tumors where earlier line use had demonstrated preserved or

697
00:41:54.104 --> 00:41:56.744
improved activity, including DESTINY-Breast09.

698
00:41:57.424 --> 00:42:01.184
Importantly, prospective trials are needed to validate these findings and

699
00:42:01.204 --> 00:42:04.204
define the role of trastuzumab deruxtecan in the second-line

700
00:42:04.284 --> 00:42:07.936
setting.HER2-amplified

701
00:42:08.036 --> 00:42:11.896
microsatellite stable metastatic colorectal cancer represents a high-risk,

702
00:42:11.976 --> 00:42:14.796
low-frequency population with limited treatment options.

703
00:42:15.276 --> 00:42:19.056
In this large real-world cohort, use of trastuzumab deruxtecan in the

704
00:42:19.096 --> 00:42:23.016
second-line setting was associated with improved long-term survival

705
00:42:23.076 --> 00:42:24.796
compared with standard chemotherapy.

706
00:42:25.356 --> 00:42:29.296
With similar early outcomes but clear late divergence favoring trastuzumab

707
00:42:29.316 --> 00:42:32.456
deruxtecan. These findings extend prior Destiny

708
00:42:32.576 --> 00:42:36.476
CRC-01 and Destiny CRC-02 data into an earlier-line

709
00:42:36.716 --> 00:42:37.996
real-world treatment setting.

710
00:42:39.716 --> 00:42:43.436
I would like to sincerely thank my co-author, Dr. Sumbul Aziz, and my mentors, Dr.

711
00:42:43.676 --> 00:42:47.096
Shehla Karbaji and Dr. Kannan Tanikachalam, for their guidance and

712
00:42:47.176 --> 00:42:48.516
support.

713
00:42:56.156 --> 00:43:00.096
We welcome any questions. To

714
00:43:00.196 --> 00:43:03.896
start, you had talked about how the patients were propensity matched on

715
00:43:03.936 --> 00:43:07.036
several factors, including the prior treatment.

716
00:43:07.436 --> 00:43:10.656
Can you elaborate? Was that matching based on the drug?

717
00:43:10.716 --> 00:43:14.496
Was it based on the duration for which they had been on first-line therapy?

718
00:43:14.836 --> 00:43:18.156
So it was based on the drugs. So it was those who have received

719
00:43:18.236 --> 00:43:22.096
FOLFOX or those who have received FOLFIRI, they were matched on that basis.

720
00:43:25.276 --> 00:43:29.036
And then with time, you had commented on the curves initially being very

721
00:43:29.156 --> 00:43:32.826
similar and then separating. What was the estimated

722
00:43:32.936 --> 00:43:36.876
patient sample size as you got out to those longer time points?

723
00:43:37.276 --> 00:43:40.816
So when we were around the longer time points, we still had

724
00:43:40.856 --> 00:43:41.716
around

725
