852
00:50:24.496 --> 00:50:28.396
And a lot of the studies have been limited in small sample sizes, case-control

853
00:50:28.456 --> 00:50:31.976
designs, and residual confounding, especially on

854
00:50:32.036 --> 00:50:32.836
comorbidities.

855
00:50:34.196 --> 00:50:37.996
And just on the right side, showing what the general hypothesis is of

856
00:50:38.056 --> 00:50:41.736
these medications, indicating that ARBs have more of an

857
00:50:41.796 --> 00:50:45.336
antiproliferative and proapoptotic effect, while

858
00:50:45.416 --> 00:50:48.876
ACE are more proinflammatory and are meant to be

859
00:50:49.516 --> 00:50:50.436
proangiogenic.

860
00:50:51.736 --> 00:50:55.666
And so our objective was here to conduct a target trial emulation

861
00:50:56.416 --> 00:51:00.336
aimed to compare the risks of cancer diagnosis and mortality between

862
00:51:00.396 --> 00:51:04.166
ARBs and ACE initiators among US veterans with

863
00:51:04.176 --> 00:51:07.616
hypertension. We leveraged data from the

864
00:51:07.696 --> 00:51:11.296
VHA, which is a large longitudinal prospective

865
00:51:11.396 --> 00:51:15.336
cohort study. About 99 million US veterans

866
00:51:15.396 --> 00:51:18.936
are included, receiving care at the VA.

867
00:51:19.796 --> 00:51:21.636
On the right side, you can see that

868
00:51:22.536 --> 00:51:26.316
it's really rich electronic health record data coming from VA

869
00:51:26.356 --> 00:51:30.176
facilities, community providers, military health systems,

870
00:51:30.496 --> 00:51:34.056
pharmacies, and lab and testing. For our

871
00:51:34.096 --> 00:51:37.696
project here specifically, we used data for the exposure

872
00:51:37.716 --> 00:51:41.456
