874
00:51:45.376 --> 00:51:48.196
prescription, but then also looking at the outcome

875
00:51:49.456 --> 00:51:51.896
in the VA cancer registry and also death records.

876
00:51:53.676 --> 00:51:56.036
So I'm going to walk you through the target trial emulation

877
00:51:57.276 --> 00:52:00.476
framework. Looking at the eligibility, we had veterans

878
00:52:00.516 --> 00:52:04.396
included with hypertension initiating either of the drugs,

879
00:52:04.456 --> 00:52:07.596
so ACE or ARBs, but not at the same time.

880
00:52:08.116 --> 00:52:10.086
Early 2000 to 2017.

881
00:52:11.796 --> 00:52:15.176
And we emulated the randomization using inverse probability weighting.

882
00:52:15.616 --> 00:52:19.076
And in this large EHR data set, we had 66

883
00:52:19.756 --> 00:52:22.856
baseline confounders available to account for.

884
00:52:24.316 --> 00:52:28.056
Follow-up was from treatment initiation until cancer

885
00:52:28.096 --> 00:52:31.876
diagnosis, death, loss of follow-up, or 10 years, or the end of

886
00:52:31.936 --> 00:52:33.526
study, which was 2022.

887
00:52:34.336 --> 00:52:38.276
And for outcomes, we looked at a comprehensive set of outcomes to follow

888
00:52:38.356 --> 00:52:42.106
a competing risk framework. We looked at

889
00:52:42.136 --> 00:52:45.826
cancer diagnosis, where death was the competing

890
00:52:45.916 --> 00:52:49.536
event, diagnosis-free mortality, where cancer was the competing event,

891
00:52:49.976 --> 00:52:53.956
all-cause mortality, and then a composite outcome of cancer diagnosis and

892
00:52:54.016 --> 00:52:55.976
diagnosis-free mortality.

893
00:52:57.836 --> 00:53:01.386
Statistical analysis were really mainly conducted by

894
00:53:01.616 --> 00:53:05.266
Daniel Addo, who's a PhD candidate in our department,

