00:53:05.656 --> 00:53:08.606
who's about to graduate, so if anyone's looking for a postdoc.

896
00:53:09.956 --> 00:53:13.716
We computed cumulative incidence, risk ratios, risk differences at

897
00:53:13.756 --> 00:53:15.436
various time points up to 10 years,

898
00:53:16.276 --> 00:53:19.556
and also looked at cancer subtypes by the SEER

899
00:53:19.656 --> 00:53:22.516
